## Phase 5 — Visualization
**Goal:** Provide visual feedback of the simulation via colored terminal output and optionally a graphical interface.

### 5.1 Colored terminal output (required)
- In [src/visualization.py](file:///home/smoustaj/goinfre/fly-in/src/visualization.py):
- Display the network as ASCII/Unicode art or as a zone-list per turn
- Color-code zones by type:
  - 🟢 `normal` — green
  - 🔴 `blocked` — red
  - 🟡 `restricted` — yellow
  - 🔵 `priority` — cyan
- Show drone positions with their IDs (`D1`, `D2`, etc.)
- Highlight movements with arrows or color changes
- Display turn number and statistics (drones delivered, drones waiting)

### 5.2 Graphical interface (optional, bonus)
- Use `pygame` or a browser-based approach (HTML + JS)
- Draw the network as a node-link diagram using hub coordinates
- Animate drone movements turn by turn
- Show zone capacity as fill bars
- Playback controls (play, pause, step, speed)

**Deliverable:** Running any map shows a clear, colored terminal visualization of the simulation.

