## Phase 6 — Output, Scoring & Polish
**Goal:** Ensure correct output format, compute metrics, and harden the code.

### 6.1 Output format compliance
- Each turn: `D<ID>-<zone>` for all moved drones, space-separated
- Drones in-transit to restricted zones: `D<ID>-<connection_name>`
  - Connection name format: you need to define this (e.g., `start-waypoint1`)
- Omit drones that don't move
- Stop when all drones delivered to end zone

### 6.2 Metrics display
After simulation, print:
- Total turns
- Drones moved per turn (average)
- Average turns per drone
- Total weighted path cost
- Comparison against benchmark targets

### 6.3 Error handling hardening
- Parser already handles most cases — add:
  - [max_drones](file:///home/smoustaj/goinfre/fly-in/src/parsing.py#23-27) and [max_link_capacity](file:///home/smoustaj/goinfre/fly-in/src/parsing.py#41-45) must be positive integers
  - Zone type validation (`normal`, `blocked`, `restricted`, `priority`)
  - Duplicate connection detection (`a-b` == `b-a`)
  - Graceful error messages with line numbers

### 6.4 Edge-case test maps
Create custom maps for:
- Single drone, single path
- All drones, single bottleneck (capacity = 1)
- Circular graph with no dead ends
- Map where all paths go through a restricted zone
- Map with blocked zones creating forced detours

**Deliverable:** Program passes all provided maps with correct output format and meets benchmark times.

